notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Lacuna after folio 95.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 14 22; written lines: 14 22; 14 to 15 lines a page on folios 1-18 and 89-90, and 20 to 22 on folios 19-88. Biblical text in Hebrew characters is embodied.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: A cursive Naskhi hand, of probably 13th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Commentary on Numbers. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2560.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [97v].
